						<div class="feature-grid">
							<div class="feature">
								<div class="content">
										<p>To understand just how quickly Covid-19 has spreading, we can compare the number of new deaths caused by the virus each day to the average number of deaths per day due to pneumonia and influenza during the 2017-2018 season. Over the course of a month the number of deaths per day due to Covid-19 quadrupled roughly once a week, growing from less than 100 to over 2000. Meanwhile during the one month period when pneumonia and influenza deaths were growing most for the 2017-2018 season, the average deaths per day rose from around 200 to around 450. For comparison, while it took around a month for the number of pneumonia and influenza related deaths per day to double, it took less than a week for Covid-19 related deaths per day to grow that amount.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							<div class="feature">
